Class StateUtils

public class StateUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    This class support handling of openHAB type State. Therefore, it provides the methods:
    • createState(java.lang.Object) for creating an openHAB State.

    • Method Detail

      • createState

        public static org.eclipse.smarthome.core.types.State createState(@Nullable java.lang.Object propertyValue)
        Creates an openHAB State in accordance to the class of the given propertyValue. Currently PercentType, DecimalType, and Boolean are handled explicitly. All other dataTypes are mapped to StringType.

        If propertyValue is null, UnDefType.NULL will be returned.

        Copied/adapted from the org.openhab.binding.koubachi binding.

        Parameters:
        propertyValue - which should be converted,
        Returns:
        state of type State in accordance with dataType. Will never be null.
